        <div class="prose"><p>Damn. I should've read this one after <a href="#the-legacy-of-spies">&quot;The Legacy of Spies&quot;</a>. The latter one — also by le Carré — is a prequel and sequel to &quot;The Spy…&quot;, and I would've enjoyed &quot;The Legacy…&quot; more if waiting with reading it. In any case, I loved this one: a classic spy novel with &quot;plots and counter plots&quot;, as it says on the back. I like the author's writing in the way that it's very on point. Like the world he's created, the prose is cold and without too many emotions.</p></div>

